en_76228_0	The Irrigation Department has launched a programme to control the floods that are impacting the Matara area.
en_76228_1	Accordingly an effort is being made to clean the Kiramba-Aara River which is a tertiary of the Nilwala River.
en_76228_2	Accordingly, eight kilometres from Pattare to Palolpitiya is being developed.
en_76228_3	The allocation made for this effort is two million rupees.
en_76228_4	This programme will enable to control floods that occur in several areas including Palolpitiya, Polathugoda, Vitiyala, Akurugoda and Talwatte.
en_76228_5	The Irrigation Department said that the programme which is in the final phase will be of great relief for the people as well as farming activities.
